  "why": "QATest enforces semantic consistency and naturalness at each mutation step (i.e., it validates each generated mutant against the immediate seed using ROUGE-1 and uses a perplexity-based priority to retain authentic, natural sentences). However, the framework performs iterative mutations and accepts mutants based on similarity to the most recent seed (and on perplexity computed from the current seed set), without an explicit check that each mutant remains similar to the original seed across multiple iterations. Thus QATest preserves plausibility between successive steps but does not explicitly prevent cumulative drift relative to the original seed.",
